Subject: Re: Chroma keying..
From: Hans-Joerg Frieden <hfrieden@uni-trier.de>
Date: Wed, 1 Mar 2000 12:33:15 +0100 (CET)

On Tue, 29 Feb 2000, fRaC^tioN wrote:

> could ne1 explain me briefly what x-actly 'chroma keying' is (might b this
> is a useful effect for my demo-engine ;)?

With W3D V3,  you can specify a range of  colors (lower-upper) that is
to be  considered transparent, i.e. there  are no pixels  drawn when a
color  of this range  is encountered  (or vice  versa, depends  on the
mode). This is different from  full transparency in the respect that a
chroma-keyed  pixel  is *never*  drawn,  i.e.  it  does not  fill  the
ZBuffer, while a  100% transparent pixel still fills  the ZBuffer with
its depth coordinate... 

On  the permedia2,  the  color range  is  limited to  a single  color,
i.e. only one  border of the range is really used.  On the ViRGE, this
thing is not supported at all... 

