You  can  pass individual  triangles  using multiple  W3D_DrawTriangle
calls  only. For strips  and fans,  there is  the W3D_DrawTriStrip/Fan
functions that really do use the feature of drawing continously if the
chip supports it.=20

There is currently  no way of drawing a  list of individual trianlges,
and I  don't think this will be  too much of an  improvement since the
call will  overlap with the drawing operation.  Drawing triangle stips
and  fans   is  fastest  since   it  requires  the  least   amount  of
vertices. Other  than that, each  vertex must be uploaded  anyway, and
there is no way of using an array of vertices and referencing vertices
by index...=20

